  Update description to match mixed eclass usage.

  17 Apr 2013; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jnrowe-github.eclass:
  Update GitHub download location.

  26 Nov 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jnrowe-pypi.eclass:
  Switched to EAPI-5.

  26 Nov 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jnrowe-github.eclass:
  Supports EAPI-5.

  25 Oct 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jnrowe-pypi.eclass:
  Default to distutils-r1.

  29 May 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jnrowe-pypi.eclass:
  Depend on unzip if archive is a zip file. [Workaround purely for those using
  portage.]

  09 Apr 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jnrowe-pypi.eclass:
  Call base_src_prepare in jnrowe-pypi's src_install when using
  python-distutils-ng.

  09 Apr 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jnrowe-pypi.eclass:
  Call default in src_install, basically just for DOCS usage.

  08 Apr 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jnrowe-pypi.eclass:
  Added python-distutils-ng support to jnrowe-pypi eclass.

  20 Mar 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jnrowe-github.eclass:
  Use vcs-import instead of custom src_unpack, it is slightly less rigorous but
  should work in almost all cases [580].

  18 Mar 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jnrowe-pypi.eclass:
  Support EAPI4.

  18 Mar 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jnrowe-github.eclass:
  [QA] Fixed typo

  25 Oct 2011; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jnrowe-github.eclass,
